I can't build flutter apps on my Redmi 9A Android version 10(API 29) gradle keeps failing and
even when it starts downloading it still fails sometimes takes unexpectedly long moments when downloading

## Version information

Android Studio `Chipmunk | 2021.2.1` • Flutter plugin `io.flutter 67.1.2` • Dart plugin `212.5744`

Error getting Flutter sdk information.
Flutter 3.3.1

comment_data.body: Your software is out of date. Try updating everything to the latest version and see if that helps. If it doesn't, it is likely your problem is with the [Flutter SDK](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues), not this plugin. Please let us know if that helps.

Ok! I see now, So I always have to been online for a gradle session. But why must I be always online for gradle to download artifacts?

Isn't there a way to run gradle offline mode without necessarily always being online?

Got the issue, solved I just had to connect to the internet and wait for a while
Glad to hear you got things working.

Thanks for your reply
